items.sentence: Tom didn't realize that Mary wanted to do that.
I can't believe Tom agreed to do that with you.
Do you think Tom would teach me how to do that?
I don't think Tom is old enough to do that yet.
I warned you what would happen if you did that.
Am I correct in assuming you regret doing that?
I wonder if Tom still remembers how to do that.
It would be great if we could do that together.
We might be able to do that without Tom's help.
How was I supposed to do that without any help?
